-- U.A.E. Central Bank Appoints Mundell, Dodge, Yam, Bond to Advisory Council
-- B y   I n a l   E r s a n
-- 2010-10-19T12:23:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/u-a-e-central-bank-appoints-mundell-dodge-yam-bond-to-advisory-council.html
The United Arab Emirates’ central
bank appointed Robert Mundell, David Dodge, Joseph Yam and Sir
John Bond to its international advisory council, according to an
e-mailed statement today.  “In a world of highly challenging and rapidly changing
financial landscape, the U.A.E. Central Bank needs to learn from
the experiences of this group to improve the U.A.E.’s financial
and monetary stability and Central Bank governance,” the bank
said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
